<head>INACTIVE</head>
    <list type="translations">
        <item xml:lang="zh">無動作</item>
    </list>
<div type="definition">
<p>REFUSE to ACT AND THEREFORE be PEACEFUL.</p>
    </div>
<div type="notes">
<div type="old-chinese-criteria">
<p>1. The standard general word for remaining inactive is jìng 靜 (ant. dòng 動 "take an initiative")</p>
<p>2. Wú wéi 無為 (ant. yǒu suǒ wéi 有所為 "engage in assertive action") is a technical philosophical term referring to the refusal to take assertive action.</p>
        </div>
<div type="modern-chinese-criteria">
<p>無為</p>
<p>動彈不得</p>
<p>first rough draft to identify synonym group members for future analysis, based on CL. 18.11.2003. CH</p>
        </div>
    </div>
